2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a local search algorithm for optimization problems, which is a core topic in this sub-category.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper presents a method for finding high-quality solutions to hard optimization problems, which is a common goal in AI research.
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with optimization problems that involve discrete variables, which is a key area of study in this sub-category.
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm on various constrained optimization problems, which is a topic of interest in computational complexity theory.
